12  RobotPlanningExecution::RobotPlanningExecution(
13  const std::string groupname, const double max_vel_scale_factor,
14  const int num_planning_attempts, const int planning_time,
15  const RobotOptionFlag options)
16  : move_group_(groupname), options_(options) {
17  assert(max_vel_scale_factor >= 0.0 && max_vel_scale_factor <= 1.0);
18  assert(num_planning_attempts > 0);
19  assert(planning_time > 0);
20 
21  ros::NodeHandle nodeHandler;
22  ros::Publisher display_publisher = nodeHandler.advertise<moveit_msgs::DisplayTrajectory>(
23  "/MoveGroup/display_planned_path", 1, true);
24 
25  this->move_group_.setMaxVelocityScalingFactor(max_vel_scale_factor);
26  this->move_group_.setNumPlanningAttempts(num_planning_attempts);
27  this->move_group_.setPlanningTime(planning_time);
28 
29  if (this->isOption(ROBOT_OPTION_VERBOSE_INFO)) {
30  ROS_INFO("Initialized robot");
31  ROS_INFO("\tname: %s", groupname.c_str());
32  ROS_INFO("\tmax_vel_scale_factor: %f", max_vel_scale_factor);
33  ROS_INFO("\tnum_planning_attempts: %d", num_planning_attempts);
34  ROS_INFO("\tplanning_time: %d", planning_time);
35  ROS_INFO("\toptions: %s", RobotOptionFlagToString(options).c_str());
36  }
37  }

40  return this->move_group_.getCurrentPose().pose;

43 // All plan functions will plan a linear trajectory to the give pose and output the resulting plan
44 // in the trajectory_plan variable.
45 // The returned value is the fraction of the plan which is feasible.
46  const double RobotPlanningExecution::planPoseByPose(
47  const geometry_msgs::Pose &target_pose,
48  moveit::planning_interface::MoveGroup::Plan *trajectory_plan) const {
49  std::vector<geometry_msgs::Pose> waypoints;
50 
51  waypoints.push_back(this->getCurrentPose());
52  waypoints.push_back(target_pose);
53  moveit_msgs::RobotTrajectory trajectory;
54  double fraction = this->move_group_.computeCartesianPath(
55  waypoints,
56  0.01, // eef_step
57  0.0, // jump_threshold
58  trajectory);
59 
60  if (trajectory_plan != NULL) {
61  trajectory_plan->trajectory_ = trajectory;
62  }
63 
64  if (this->isOption(ROBOT_OPTION_VERBOSE_INFO)) {
65  ROS_INFO("Visualizing plan (%.2f%% acheived)", fraction * 100.0);
66  ROS_INFO("POSE: \n\tPos: x=%f, y=%f, z=%f,\n\t Rot: x=%f, y=%f, z=%f, w=%f",
67  target_pose.position.x,
68  target_pose.position.y,
69  target_pose.position.z,
70  target_pose.orientation.x,
71  target_pose.orientation.y,
72  target_pose.orientation.z,
73  target_pose.orientation.w);
74  if (fraction < 1.0) {
75  ROS_WARN("Plan not fully feasible");
76  }
77  }
78 
79  return fraction;
80  }

82  const double RobotPlanningExecution::planPoseByXYZRPY(
83  const double pos_x, const double pos_y, const double pos_z,
84  const double rot_r, const double rot_p, const double rot_y,
85  moveit::planning_interface::MoveGroup::Plan *trajectory_plan) const {
86  geometry_msgs::Pose target_pose;
87  target_pose.position.x = pos_x;
88  target_pose.position.y = pos_y;
89  target_pose.position.z = pos_z;
90  target_pose.orientation = this->QuaternionFromRPY(rot_r, rot_p, rot_y);
91  return this->planPoseByPose(target_pose, trajectory_plan);
92  }

94  const double RobotPlanningExecution::planRelativePoseByXYZRPY(
95  const double pos_x, const double pos_y, const double pos_z,
96  const double rot_r, const double rot_p, const double rot_y,

164 // All goTo functions will plan a linear trajectory to the given pose and execute the plan
165 // The returned value is the fraction of plan which is feasible.
166  const double RobotPlanningExecution::goToPoseByPose(const geometry_msgs::Pose &target_pose) const {
167  moveit::planning_interface::MoveGroup::Plan trajectory_plan;
168  double fraction = this->planPoseByPose(target_pose, &trajectory_plan);
169  if (this->isOption(ROBOT_OPTION_VERBOSE_INFO)) {
170  ROS_INFO("Executing plan");
171  }
172  if (fraction < 1.0) {
173  ROS_ERROR("Plan not fully feasible");
174  }
175  if (!this->isOption(ROBOT_OPTION_DUMMY_ROBOT)) {
176  this->move_group_.execute(trajectory_plan);
177  }
178  ros::Duration(0.5).sleep();
179  return fraction;
180  }

332  const geometry_msgs::Quaternion RobotPlanningExecution::AddRPYToQuaternion(
333  const double roll, const double pitch, const double yaw, const geometry_msgs::Quaternion &q) const {
334  tf::Quaternion add_tf = tf::createQuaternionFromRPY(roll, pitch, yaw);
335  tf::Quaternion q_tf;
336  tf::quaternionMsgToTF(q, q_tf);
337  q_tf *= add_tf;
338  geometry_msgs::Quaternion result;
339  tf::quaternionTFToMsg(q_tf, result);
340  return result;
341  }
